# AdGo — AI Ad Automation Platform

An AI-driven ad automation platform: a business describes itself, Claude generates an ad
strategy (audiences, budget split, creatives), a campaign orchestrator launches it across
Meta and Google, a performance pipeline ingests results, a bandit-based optimization engine
reallocates budget toward winners, and a billing engine invoices usage-based fees.

## Architecture

```
apps/web        Frontend — onboarding + dashboard (React/Vite)
apps/api        Backend — single Express service composed of modular units:
  gateway/        Auth (JWT) + rate limiting + routing
  modules/strategy/      Claude-based strategy generation (falls back to a
                         deterministic mock if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is unset)
  modules/orchestrator/  Builds campaigns from a strategy, launches/pauses
                         variants via ad network adapters
  modules/adapters/      Meta + Google Ads clients (mock data unless live
                         credentials are configured — see below)
  modules/pipeline/      Ingests raw ad-network insights, normalizes into
                         CTR / conversion rate / CPA per variant
  modules/optimization/  Epsilon-greedy bandit: exploits the best-scoring
                         variant, explores others, pauses high-CPA variants
  modules/billing/       Usage-based invoicing: flat fee + % of ad spend
```

Data is persisted to a local SQLite file at `apps/api/data/adgo.sqlite` (created on first run).

## Setup

```bash
npm install
cp apps/api/.env.example apps/api/.env   # fill in keys you have; all are optional
npm run dev:api    # http://localhost:4000
npm run dev:web    # http://localhost:5173 (or next free port)
```

Open the web app, complete onboarding, generate a strategy, and launch a campaign. Use
"Pull latest metrics" and "Run optimization pass" on a campaign's detail page to exercise
the performance/optimization feedback loop, and generate an invoice from the Billing page.

### Environment variables (`apps/api/.env`)

All external integrations are optional in development — every adapter falls back to
deterministic mock data so the full flow works with zero configuration:

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — enables real Claude-generated strategies (Claude Sonnet 5)
- `META_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `META_AD_ACCOUNT_ID` — enables live Meta Marketing API calls
- `GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN`, `GOOGLE_ADS_CUSTOMER_ID`, `GOOGLE_ADS_ACCESS_TOKEN` — enables live Google Ads API calls

## Data model (Postgres / Prisma)

`apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma` defines the target production schema: Organization/User
(tenancy), Business + ScrapedPage (onboarding), OAuthConnection (encrypted-at-rest tokens),
Strategy + Creative (AI output, held in DRAFT/IN_REVIEW until approved), Campaign +
CampaignCreative (per-network launch state), Metric (daily performance, designed to become
a TimescaleDB hypertable at volume), OptimizationAction (audit log of every automated
pause/budget change), Notification, and Subscription/UsageRecord/Invoice (Stripe-backed
usage billing). A generated initial migration lives at
`apps/api/prisma/migrations/20260703000000_init/migration.sql`.

This schema is **not yet wired into the running app** — the working prototype still uses
the simpler SQLite/JSON-blob store in `apps/api/src/db/`. Migrating the modules under
`apps/api/src/modules/` to read/write through Prisma against Postgres is the next step
before any of the OAuth, scraping, or Stripe work lands.

To point it at a real database: set `DATABASE_URL` in `apps/api/.env`, then run
`npm run db:migrate --workspace apps/api`.

## Notes

This is an original scaffold built around the product category adsgo.ai operates in
(AI-generated ad strategy + cross-network automation), not a copy of its code, text, or
design assets.
